main event: Two observers watched star-like objects travel across the sky at different times on April 10, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were reported to fade out of sight after about 15 minutes of observation., Both observers noted that the objects moved similarly across the sky., The sightings occurred shortly after two satellites, Echo I and Echo II, were recorded in the area., The sighting location had high clouds reportedly affecting visibility., No photographs or physical evidence were collected during the observation.
